1
00:00:00,125 --> 00:00:02,083
When they brought me in from outside, there were three people

2
00:00:02,834 --> 00:00:06,334
And from here to inside, one person escorted me

3
00:00:08,792 --> 00:00:10,792
One of them escorted me from there to here

4
00:00:11,083 --> 00:00:12,751
And the ones who brought me here were three people

5
00:00:14,375 --> 00:00:16,959
They took me to the door, left me, and left

6
00:00:18,667 --> 00:00:20,292
We entered and sat inside

7
00:00:26,918 --> 00:00:29,375
The interrogation room was here

8
00:00:39,209 --> 00:00:40,792
This is the interrogation room

9
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:44,959
There was a table at the front of the room and one person sitting

10
00:00:46,083 --> 00:00:51,459
And there were a number of people sitting here, and others standing

11
00:00:52,083 --> 00:00:53,584
Waiting to be punished

12
00:00:53,792 --> 00:00:55,667
Or to be interrogated for something they had done

13
00:00:56,792 --> 00:00:59,375
When I came, I was standing here next to the door

14
00:01:00,709 --> 00:01:02,167
Later he asked me, What’s your charge

15
00:01:03,626 --> 00:01:08,250
The one outside told him they brought me in on the charge of smoking

16
00:01:09,417 --> 00:01:11,876
He brought me inside and told me, Sit down

17
00:01:13,834 --> 00:01:15,209
And he started interrogating me

18
00:01:16,375 --> 00:01:18,959
He started interrogating me about why I smoke

19
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:21,209
And why I don’t pray

20
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:27,500
Why did you stay here, and why didn’t you leave

21
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:29,959
Why were you in the areas of the apostates

22
00:01:30,667 --> 00:01:32,334
That’s how their interrogation was

23
00:01:33,667 --> 00:01:35,334
I told him I had been a smoker for a long time

24
00:01:36,334 --> 00:01:40,250
I had been smoking for a long time, I couldn’t stop suddenly

25
00:01:42,667 --> 00:01:44,959
He asked me, Can’t you quit, and I answered, I can’t

26
00:01:46,792 --> 00:01:50,292
So he told them to take me to prison and whip me ten lashes

27
00:01:51,209 --> 00:01:53,667
They took me, whipped me ten lashes, and put me in prison

28
00:01:55,417 --> 00:01:57,709
The prison was on the other side

29
00:01:59,626 --> 00:02:01,459
The one who interrogated me was one person

30
00:02:02,042 --> 00:02:04,125
And in this room there was only one person

31
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:07,542
They had a walkie-talkie to communicate with each other

32
00:02:08,751 --> 00:02:12,292
When he needed something, he called them and they came immediately

33
00:02:12,667 --> 00:02:14,792
If he needed something, he called them directly

34
00:02:15,209 --> 00:02:19,876
But in the interrogation there was one person, and he spoke Arabic

35
00:02:21,167 --> 00:02:24,375
I don’t know if he was from Mosul, or an Arab, or from somewhere else

36
00:02:24,667 --> 00:02:26,209
Or Kurdish, I don’t know exactly

37
00:02:26,918 --> 00:02:29,417
I don’t know where he was from, honestly

38
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:35,626
Because the long beard doesn’t let you tell a man’s age from his face

39
00:02:37,876 --> 00:02:42,834
And on the other hand, when he interrogates you, he sends you off right away

40
00:02:42,876 --> 00:02:48,334
It doesn’t take long, and he doesn’t let you talk or explain too much

41
00:02:49,209 --> 00:02:52,959
If you talk too much, he whips you more

42
00:02:55,083 --> 00:02:56,834
Interviewer: How many times were you interrogated?

43
00:02:56,959 --> 00:02:58,751
I was interrogated three times

44
00:02:59,959 --> 00:03:03,500
The first time here, the second time somewhere else

45
00:03:03,959 --> 00:03:06,792
And the third time they interrogated me in the street and put me in prison

46
00:03:11,667 --> 00:03:16,250
Interviewer: When you arrived the first time

47
00:03:16,918 --> 00:03:21,792
And the second time, was it in the same room?

48
00:03:21,876 --> 00:03:26,375
No, here only once, the second time was in a house

49
00:03:26,959 --> 00:03:28,876
A family lives in it now

50
00:03:30,542 --> 00:03:35,083
Now we can’t go to that house so I can explain to you, because a family lives there

51
00:03:35,834 --> 00:03:39,626
The second time was in the house, they were settled there

52
00:03:40,042 --> 00:03:41,334
And it was turned into an interrogation place

53
00:03:42,375 --> 00:03:44,584
Here was the first time, there was the second time

54
00:03:45,709 --> 00:03:48,292
And the third time, without interrogation, straight to prison

55
00:03:49,626 --> 00:03:52,500
When we entered, my eyes were open

56
00:03:53,417 --> 00:03:55,834
When he asked what charge they’d brought me for

57
00:03:55,834 --> 00:03:57,417
And they told him smoking, he said to me, Sit down

58
00:03:58,167 --> 00:04:00,209
There were chairs we sat on

59
00:04:00,834 --> 00:04:02,751
And there were people being interrogated

60
00:04:03,667 --> 00:04:05,626
And there were people filing complaints

61
00:04:07,250 --> 00:04:08,459
I don’t know who they were

62
00:04:09,542 --> 00:04:11,334
When they left, he started interrogating me

63
00:04:12,834 --> 00:04:16,375
And when he finished interrogating me, they took me to prison

64
00:04:17,125 --> 00:04:18,459
The interrogation didn’t take long

65
00:04:21,792 --> 00:04:27,042
Interviewer: Was the interrogation recorded, or was someone filming you?

66
00:04:27,209 --> 00:04:31,542
Or was your trial recorded with a camera or an audio recorder?

67
00:04:32,417 --> 00:04:34,417
Honestly no, I didn’t notice

68
00:04:35,083 --> 00:04:36,834
We didn’t notice that

69
00:04:37,292 --> 00:04:39,375
As for recording, no one was recording

70
00:04:39,876 --> 00:04:42,042
They just talk to you, that’s all

71
00:04:43,876 --> 00:04:48,083
Interviewer: Were you threatened by the interrogator?

72
00:04:51,375 --> 00:04:55,959
Did he threaten you with beating, whipping, or execution?

73
00:04:56,292 --> 00:04:58,584
Or did he threaten you with long prison terms during interrogation?

74
00:04:59,334 --> 00:05:02,709
Yes, of course, he didn’t threaten me

75
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:08,417
But he ordered me to be whipped during the interrogation

76
00:05:09,292 --> 00:05:12,542
And he told me if I kept smoking and was caught

77
00:05:12,667 --> 00:05:13,834
They’d whip me more

78
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:15,667
More additional lashes

79
00:05:16,167 --> 00:05:17,542
If now it was 20 lashes

80
00:05:18,375 --> 00:05:19,709
Next time it’d be 40 lashes

81
00:05:21,918 --> 00:05:23,292
That’s how he threatened with whipping

82
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:30,500
Interviewer: Were you threatened with harm to a family member if you repeated it?

83
00:05:31,042 --> 00:05:36,250
No, they didn’t do that, the threat was only against me

84
00:05:36,876 --> 00:05:39,334
They only threatened me with whipping or killing

85
00:05:40,417 --> 00:05:44,167
But they didn’t threaten my family

86
00:05:46,709 --> 00:05:51,000
Interviewer: Did the interrogation involve any physical or psychological torture?

87
00:05:52,167 --> 00:05:53,709
Witness: You mean how, by beating?

88
00:05:53,751 --> 00:05:56,125
Interviewer: I mean did someone come and beat you?

89
00:05:56,167 --> 00:05:59,083
Or grab you strongly for example?

90
00:05:59,542 --> 00:06:03,000
I mean, what kind of torture was it?

91
00:06:03,042 --> 00:06:07,375
Torture by beating, or psychological torture?

92
00:06:07,417 --> 00:06:08,918
Do you mean in the interrogation?
Interviewer: Yes

93
00:06:08,918 --> 00:06:14,042
The first time was a normal interrogation

94
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:17,918
But when he took me to prison

95
00:06:18,459 --> 00:06:20,500
There was also interrogation there

96
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:24,459
There was a judge upstairs in the prison

97
00:06:25,167 --> 00:06:28,209
On the second floor, and also on the ground floor

98
00:06:28,834 --> 00:06:32,334
There were interrogators they called judges, who worked for them

99
00:06:33,417 --> 00:06:35,626
The fear there was worse than here

100
00:06:40,709 --> 00:06:46,584
When they interrogated us there,
our eyes were blindfolded, not like here
